reviewText: Didn't expect much from this, just wanted to see what it looked like on my new 3-d tv... Terribly boring to begin with but even worse was that it isn't real 3D... I may have missed that part of the add but no less a disappointment.

Maybe not for everyone, but for guys who like to see girls totally undressed, being silly, I'd recommend it.  Most of the girls appeared to be natural, and they were having spontaneous ad-lib fun, not just acting out a script.  Of course the structure of the "plot," if you'd even call it that, competing to join Beverly Lynne's sorority, was absurd, but it made a good vehicle for lots of unclothed action.
not that entertaining. the girls are not really sexy or simulating, action was kind of board no climaxs. I've seen hotter sorority girls. many of them were petity.

It is nothing like the cover looks, it was so teenage / childish /stupid / everyone sitting in a room talking about things. It was like a test, they tell someone to get up and do something in front of each other or on one another. I  watched this and I was very disappointed, put it in the trash can after trying to watch for the 1st time. And no 3d effects, if there was you could not tell. you could see the same with glasses on or off.
